    {
      "id": "line-000",
      "start": 0.0,
      "end": 5.68,
      "text": "This is a LibraVox recording. All LibraVox recordings are in the public domain. For more",
      "note": ""
    },
    {
      "id": "line-001",
      "start": 5.68,
      "end": 9.92,
      "text": "information or to volunteer, please visit LibraVox.org.",
      "note": ""
    },
    {
      "id": "line-002",
      "start": 10.78,
      "end": 14.58,
      "text": "Recorded by Lee Dunkelberg, Fort Worth, Texas, Dunkelberg.com",
      "note": ""
    },
    {
      "id": "line-003",
      "start": 15.44,
      "end": 18.1,
      "text": "Asop's Fables, the Soldier, and his Horse.",
      "note": ""
    },
    {
      "id": "line-004",
      "start": 19.52,
      "end": 29.98,
      "text": "A Soldier gave a Horse a plentiful supply of oats in time of war and tended him with the",
      "note": ""
    },
    {
      "id": "line-005",
      "start": 29.98,
      "end": 35.78,
      "text": "wild and swift to bear his master when need arose out of the reach of danger.",
      "note": ""
    },
    {
      "id": "line-006",
      "start": 37.08,
      "end": 45.66,
      "text": "But when the war was over, he employed him on all sorts of drudgery, bestowing but little",
      "note": ""
    },
    {
      "id": "line-007",
      "start": 45.66,
      "end": 51.82,
      "text": "attention upon him and giving him more ever nothing but chaff to eat.",
      "note": ""
    },
    {
      "id": "line-008",
      "start": 52.88,
      "end": 58.36,
      "text": "The time came when war broke out again and a Soldier settled in Bridal's Horse and,",
      "note": ""
    },
    {
      "id": "line-009",
      "start": 58.36,
      "end": 63.58,
      "text": "and, having put on his heavy coat of mail, mounted him to ride off and take the field.",
      "note": ""
    },
    {
      "id": "line-010",
      "start": 64.8,
      "end": 72.12,
      "text": "But the poor, half-starved beast sank down under his weight and said to his rider,",
      "note": ""
    },
    {
      "id": "line-011",
      "start": 72.6,
      "end": 79.92,
      "text": "You will have to go into battle on foot this time. Thanks to hard work and bad food, you",
      "note": ""
    },
    {
      "id": "line-012",
      "start": 79.92,
      "end": 87.64,
      "text": "have turned me from a horse into an ass, and you cannot, in a moment, turn me back again",
      "note": ""
    },
    {
      "id": "line-013",
      "start": 87.64,
      "end": 89.42,
      "text": "into a horse.",
      "note": ""
    },
    {
      "id": "line-014",
      "start": 91.4,
      "end": 93.04,
      "text": "End of the Soldier and his Horse.",
      "note": ""
    }
  ],
